---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — Fabric Planning"
  description="About Khaled Chowdhury, the Fabric Whisperer, and Data Crafters — the team behind the Fabric Planning knowledge hub."
>
  <!-- ── Page hero ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="section-no">§</span> About</span>
      <h1>Built by practitioners, <span class="italic">for practitioners</span></h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── The Fabric Whisperer ──────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="slab" style="padding-top: 88px;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-profile">
        <div class="about-photo">
          <img
            src="https://media.fabricplanning.io/branding/Khaled%20Chowdhury%20Headshot.JPG"
            alt="Headshot of Khaled Chowdhury, the Fabric Whisperer"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>

        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">
            <span class="section-no">§</span> The Fabric Whisperer
          </span>
          <h2 class="page-h2" style="margin-top: 16px;">Khaled Chowdhury</h2>
          <p class="profile-role">The Fabric Whisperer | CEO &amp; Co-Founder, Data Crafters</p>
          <p class="profile-creds">
            CMA &nbsp;|&nbsp; FPAC &nbsp;|&nbsp; Certified Chief Data Officer
            (Carnegie Mellon) &nbsp;|&nbsp; Top 50 Data Analytics Professional
            (2023)
          </p>

          <div class="about-prose">
            <p>
              I spent over 15 years in FP&amp;A, living inside Excel, building
              budget models, and managing planning cycles at companies like
              Momentive, KMG, and CMC Materials. I know what it feels like to
              spend three months on a budget cycle, wrestling with broken links,
              version control nightmares, and the constant question of whether
              the numbers are right.
            </p>
            <p>
              When I founded Data Crafters, I brought that finance perspective
              into the Microsoft Fabric ecosystem. We became a Microsoft Fabric
              Featured Partner, and I started leading the Houston Fabric User
              Group. But it was always the planning side that excited me most,
              because I knew firsthand how broken the process was for most
              mid-market companies.
            </p>
            <p>
              When Microsoft announced Fabric Planning at FabCon 2026, I saw
              something I had been waiting for: a native planning capability
              built directly into the platform where the data already lives. No
              more duct-taping external tools to Power BI. No more uncertified
              custom visuals. No more paying for 200 licenses when only 50
              people are actively planning.
            </p>
            <p>
              That&rsquo;s why I built Fabric Planning (the website). This is
              not a sales pitch. This is a knowledge hub for finance and data
              professionals who want to understand what Fabric Planning can
              actually do, where the gaps are, and how to get started.
              I&rsquo;ve been in your shoes. I&rsquo;m building this because
              it&rsquo;s what I wish existed when I was evaluating tools from
              the other side of the table.
            </p>
            <p class="quiet">Use things. Love people. Worship the divine.</p>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-top: 28px;">
            <a
              class="btn btn-ghost"
              href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/khaledchowdhury/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              Connect on LinkedIn <span class="arr">→</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Collaborators ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="slab slab-elev">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose-center">
        <h2 class="page-h2" style="justify-content: center;">Collaborators</h2>
        <p>
          Fabric Planning is a collaborative effort. We&rsquo;re building a
          community of practitioners, thought leaders, and community builders
          who are passionate about Microsoft Fabric Planning. More collaborators
          coming soon.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Sponsor ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="slab">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose-center">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content: center;">
          <span class="section-no">§</span> Sponsor
        </span>
        <h2 class="page-h2" style="justify-content: center; margin-top: 18px;">
          Sponsored by Data Crafters
        </h2>
        <p>
          Data Crafters is a Microsoft Fabric Featured Partner consultancy
          serving mid-market companies across the United States. As a Solutions
          Partner for Data &amp; AI and Digital &amp; App Innovation with an
          Analytics on Azure specialization, Data Crafters helps organizations
          build their data foundation on Microsoft Fabric. Fabric Planning is an
          independent knowledge hub sponsored by Data Crafters. The content is
          community-driven and vendor-neutral.
        </p>
        <a
          class="btn btn-primary"
          href="https://datacrafters.io"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Visit datacrafters.io <span class="arr">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
